### Configure Playwright JSON Reporter Output in Configuration File (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-reporters-js.md

Set up the Playwright JSON reporter and define its output file directly within playwright.config.ts. This approach provides a persistent and version-controlled method for managing JSON report destinations.

```javascript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  reporter: [['json', { outputFile: 'results.json' }]],
});
```

--------------------------------

### Output Playwright JSON Report to File via Environment Variable

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-reporters-js.md

Direct Playwright's JSON reporter output to a specified file by setting an environment variable before running tests. This method is suitable for programmatic control over report storage across various operating systems.

```bash
PLAYWRIGHT_JSON_OUTPUT_NAME=results.json npx playwright test --reporter=json
```

```batch
set PLAYWRIGHT_JSON_OUTPUT_NAME=results.json
npx playwright test --reporter=json
```

```powershell
$env:PLAYWRIGHT_JSON_OUTPUT_NAME="results.json"
npx playwright test --reporter=json
```

--------------------------------

### Configure multiple Playwright test reporters simultaneously

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-reporters-js.md

This example shows how to configure Playwright to use multiple reporters at the same time by providing an array in the `playwright.config.ts` file. It illustrates combining a 'list' reporter for terminal output with a 'json' reporter to generate a comprehensive JSON file of test results.

```js
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  reporter: [
    ['list'],
    ['json', {  outputFile: 'test-results.json' }]
  ],
});
```

