### Configure Playwright Blob Reporter with Environment Tag (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-reporters-js.md

Extend the Blob reporter configuration in playwright.config.ts to include a global tag. This tag, often derived from an environment variable, enhances clarity in merged reports and ensures unique blob report names for different testing environments.

```javascript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  reporter: 'blob',
  tag: process.env.CI_ENVIRONMENT_NAME,  // for example "@APIv2" or "@linux"
});
```

