### Configure conditional Playwright test reporters for CI/local environments

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-reporters-js.md

This snippet demonstrates how to dynamically select a Playwright test reporter based on the execution environment, specifically differentiating between CI (Continuous Integration) and local runs. It uses `process.env.CI` to apply a concise 'dot' reporter for CI and the default 'list' reporter locally, optimizing output verbosity for each context.

```js
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  // Concise 'dot' for CI, default 'list' when running locally
  reporter: process.env.CI ? 'dot' : 'list',
});
```

