### Generate Istanbul Report from Playwright JavaScript Coverage (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/class-coverage.md

This example demonstrates how to capture JavaScript code coverage using Playwright's `Coverage` API and convert the V8 coverage output into an Istanbul-compatible report. It launches a Chromium browser, navigates to a URL, collects coverage data, and then processes each entry using the `v8toIstanbul` library, logging the resulting Istanbul report to the console. This functionality is supported only on Chromium-based browsers.

```javascript
const { chromium } = require('playwright');
const v8toIstanbul = require('v8-to-istanbul');

(async () => {
  const browser = await chromium.launch();
  const page = await browser.newPage();
  await page.coverage.startJSCoverage();
  await page.goto('https://chromium.org');
  const coverage = await page.coverage.stopJSCoverage();
  for (const entry of coverage) {
    const converter = v8toIstanbul('', 0, { source: entry.source });
    await converter.load();
    converter.applyCoverage(entry.functions);
    console.log(JSON.stringify(converter.toIstanbul()));
  }
  await browser.close();
})();
```

