### Mocking JSON WebSocket Communication

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/class-websocketroute.md

Illustrates how to handle and respond to JSON-formatted WebSocket messages, parsing incoming JSON and sending back structured JSON responses.

```APIDOC
## Mocking JSON WebSocket Communication

### Description
This example extends basic mocking to handle JSON messages. It demonstrates parsing an incoming JSON message, checking its content, and then constructing and sending a JSON response. This is useful for simulating complex client-server interactions.

### API Method
`page.routeWebSocket(url, handler)`

### Parameters
#### Callback Parameters
- **ws** (`WebSocketRoute`) - Required - The WebSocketRoute instance for the routed WebSocket.

### Example Usage (JavaScript)
```js
await page.routeWebSocket('wss://example.com/ws', ws => {
  ws.onMessage(message => {
    const json = JSON.parse(message);
    if (json.request === 'question')
      ws.send(JSON.stringify({ response: 'answer' }));
  });
});
```
### Example Usage (Java)
```java
page.routeWebSocket("wss://example.com/ws", ws -> {
  ws.onMessage(frame -> {
    JsonObject json = new JsonParser().parse(frame.text()).getAsJsonObject();
    if ("question".equals(json.get("request").getAsString())) {
      Map<String, String> result = new HashMap();
      result.put("response", "answer");
      ws.send(gson.toJson(result));
    }
  });
});
```
### Example Usage (Python Async)
```python async
def message_handler(ws: WebSocketRoute, message: Union[str, bytes]):
  json_message = json.loads(message)
  if json_message["request"] == "question":
    ws.send(json.dumps({ "response": "answer" }))

await page.route_web_socket("wss://example.com/ws", lambda ws: ws.on_message(
    lambda message: message_handler(ws, message)
))
```
### Example Usage (Python Sync)
```python sync
